Science and scientific methods. Research problem. Methods. Resaerch questions. Research aim. Validity and reliability in scientific research. Hypotheses. Sample and sampling methods. Quantitative and qualitative methods. Research ethics. Design of research.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of diploma thesis seminar is to give students basic knowledge for carrying out social research: social research methods, work with data bases and data analyze methods.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student:  1) knows theoretical and strategical approaches and juridical regulations in the field student was chosen for research; 2) knows ethical and confidential principles for carrying out the research; 3) knows social empirical research principles; 4) is qualified for independent work with data bases; 5) specific research methods for conducting the research; 6) knows procedures for protecting research work; 7) can work with databases, can understand data from research conducted by others, can evaluate results and use data correctly, can prepare a research method and supervise the conduct of the research; 8) carry out independent research in social field; 9) analyze correctly research data; 10) interpret research data.
